<TEXT>
iraq will have until jan 15 to withdraw 
its troops from kuwait before it faces the prospect of 
unauthorized military action the soviet un ambassador said 
tuesday 
yes its going to be the 15th ambassador yuli m vorontsov 
replied when asked if there was a consensus among the five 
permanent members of the security council on a resolution 
but wednesday in beijing foreign minister qian qichen said 
china will not vote for the un resolution 
qian however refused to say whether china will veto the 
resolution expected to come to a vote on thursday or abstain 
as one of the permanent members of the un security council 
china has veto power over any resolution it has voted for all 10 
previous resolutions that seek to pressure iraq to end its nearly 
4monthold occupation of kuwait but has said it does not want 
force used 
it has always been the position of china to call for a 
peaceful settlement qian told reporters at the beijing airport 
while preparing to leave for the united states to cast chinas 
vote 
secretary of state james a baker iii and soviet foreign 
minister eduard shevardnadze fixed the deadline in the last 24 
hours said western diplomats speaking on condition of anonymity 
the measure will authorize all necessary means to get iraq 
out of kuwait after that deadline the date after which a military 
strike could begin had been the only unresolved issue in the draft 
measure 
the united states had already secured agreement on the overall 
measure from the soviets french british and it was thought 
the chinese the draft resolution has more than enough pledges of 
positive votes to pass when it comes before the full council 
most security council members are expected to be represented by 
their foreign ministers at thursdays meeting with baker 
presiding 
a resolution requires at least nine votes to pass so long as 
none of the permanent members vetoes it 
the measure is supported by at least six of the nonpermanent 
council members canada finland romania ivory coast zaire 
ethiopia 
initially the united states had pressed for a jan 1 deadline 
but the soviets wanted it set at jan 31 to allow more time for 
diplomatic maneuvers 
us reinforcements on their way to the persian gulf will not be 
ready for a military strike before late january or february in any 
case diplomats said 
the measure would call on iraq to release all foreign hostages 
withdraw its troops and restore kuwaits government by jan 15 
if iraq fails to comply it would authorize member states 
cooperating with the government of kuwait to use all necessary 
means to uphold and implement the security council resolutions 
passed in response to iraqs invasion and occupation of kuwait and 
to restore international peace and security 
the resolution cites chapter 7 of the un charter which 
authorizes the use of military force to counter aggression if 
sanctions and other steps fail 
the only other time military force was sanctioned by the united 
nations to counter aggression was in 1950 during the korean 
conflict 
cuban ambassador ricardo alarcon said his country could not 
support it yemen the councils only arab member is believed 
likely to abstain or vote against it 
malaysia and colombias votes are uncertain colombias foreign 
minister said tuesday his government was still undecided 
