<TEXT>
a beneficial natural fungus that attacks two 
costly plant diseases has been approved by the government for 
commercial use in greenhouses 
the agriculture department said the fungus a strain of 
gliocladium virens has been approved by the environmental 
protection agency as a greenhouse biological control of two harmful 
fungi that cause damping off diseases 
according to the departments agricultural research service it 
is the first time in the united states a biocontrol fungus has been 
approved for use against a plant disease 
dampingoff diseases cause rotting of seeds seedlings and 
cuttings losses are estimated at more than 1 billion a year 
the research service said its scientists invented and patented 
the technology for formulating the good fungus gliocladium into 
easily applied pellets wr grace amp co was granted an exclusive 
license for its use 
grace developed the technology further and hopes to have a 
product on the market in two years eventually the company said it 
may seek epa approval for using the pellets outdoors as markets 
develop 
the research service said monday that dampingoff fungi are 
attacked by the pellets rhizoctonia solani and pythium ultimum 
the diseases can destroy 10 percent to 30 percent of a crop 
among dampingoffs victims are geraniums snapdragons 
chrysanthemums celosia poinsettias cotton corn beans and 
soybeans 
tests performed by usda plant pathologists robert d lumsden and 
james c locke show plant losses caused by dampingoff were reduced 
by 80 percent to 95 percent which are similar to results gained 
from the use of chemical fungicides 
the agency said further improvements are being sought to reduce 
losses 95 percent or even 100 percent 
approval by epa allows gliocladiums use on any plants grown in 
a greenhouse including ornamentals and edibles such as tomatoes 
cabbage or broccoli 
the pellets resemble granular fertilizer and are made of dormant 
fungi spores wheat bran and alginate a natural gellike material 
that binds the particle together 
when the pellets are moistened the spores germinate and the 
fungus multiplies and controls the disease the agency said 
gliocladium was described as a naturally occurring organism 
that was isolated from maryland soil in the early 1980s at the 
agencys biocontrol of plant diseases laboratory in beltsville md 
 
washington ap the agriculture department has concluded a 
national hearing on possible changes in the pricing procedures 
under the nations 42 federal milk marketing orders 
but department officials say it will be well into next year 
before a final proposal can be drawn up for public comment 
more than 10000 pages of comments were taken from 195 witnesses 
during the 43 days of testimony that began sept 5 in eau claire 
wis and concluded nov 20 in irving texas 
the department sid monday a complete transcript of the hearing 
is being compiled copies are expected to be available by 
middecember for public inspection at the 16 federal milk marketing 
order offices across the country 
briefs based on the hearing record will be allowed to be filed 
with usdas hearing clerk no later than april 13 1991 replies 
will be accepted by april 27 
after april 27 the department will evaluate the evidence and 
briefs prepare a recommended decision on the proposals which 
will be open for public comment after that a final rule will 
be prepared 
any changes that rule might propose would be contingent on 
referendums in each milk marketing area a proposal would affect 
the department said 
the procedure involves the milk pricing provisions used in all 
federal milk marketing orders the system used to set minimum 
prices for milk that wholesalers must pay producers 
although the marketing orders do not set retail milk prices the 
minimums specified at the farm level are felt through the marketing 
chain 
 
