<TEXT>
here are some facts about singapore which 
swears in a new prime minister on wednesday 
 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
leadership the outgoing prime minister is lee kuan yew who has 
been prime minister for 31 years he is succeeded by goh chok tong 
who was a deputy prime minister 
 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
land singapore a former british crown colony is a southeast 
asian republic consisting of the main island and 57 smaller islands 
within its territorial waters located 85 miles north of the 
equator it is linked to the malay peninsula by road and railway 
across a causeway the total land area is 2395 square miles 
 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
people more than 76 percent of singapores 27 million people 
are ethnic chinese malays make up 15 percent and indians 6 
percent the official languages are english mandarin malay and 
tamil malay is the national language and english the language of 
administration literacy is 88 percent 
 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
politics lee kuan yews peoples action party took power with 
independence in 1959 amid strong anticolonial sentiment and with 
the help of the communists whom the pap later purged the pap has 
been returned to power in eight consecutive elections and controls 
80 of the 81 elected seats in parliament voting is compulsory for 
citizens 21 or older 
 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
economy with an average per capita annual income of 10500 
singapore enjoys one of the highest standards of living in asia 
gross domestic product increased from 36 million in 1957 to 285 
billion last year singapore is a hub for international shipping 
airlines oil refining and financial services 
 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
history in 1819 sir stamford raffles established a british 
trading base that soon attracted migrating chinese peasants it was 
occupied by the japanese for 3 years in world war ii and became a 
british crown colony in 1946 it became a selfgoverning state in 
1959 singapore joined peninsular malaysia sarawak and sabah in 
the federation of malaysia in 1963 but withdrew in 1965 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

