<TEXT>
the 1991 spoleto festival usa will 
include an 80th birthday gala for gian carlo menotti and feature 
the composer conducting one of his own operas 
only last month menotti was offering to resign as artistic 
director of the festival he brought to charleston in 1977 he later 
agreed to continue under his current contract for two more seasons 
and his dispute with the festivals board appears resolved 
it would be entirely inappropriate to have a birthday party at 
which the honoree didnt come said ross markwardt the chairman 
of the spoleto board 
menotti was in scotland and did not attend mondays news 
conference announcing the schedule however menotti generally has 
not attended program announcements 
markwardt said the dispute hasnt affected fund raising for the 
57 million festival we find no evidence the artistic content 
of this festival has been compromised he said 
the festival which runs from may 23 through june 9 will include 
three operas including menotti directing his maria golovin 
it is one of his favorite operas and one he thinks has been 
unfairly neglected said nigel redden festival general manager 
a preview on may 23 will be followed by a reception honoring 
menottis birthday the schedule also includes a birthday concert 
for menotti featuring cellist and conductor mstislav rostropovich 
menotti turns 80 july 7 
other operas at next years festival include tales of 
hoffmann and monteverdis the coronation of poppea 
the national ballet of spain and the rambert dance company from 
england will lend an international feeling to next years festival 
the dance program includes the festival of indonesia in 
performance the troupe includes dancers and a 20piece 
percussion orchestra 
dance premieres at spoleto include works by the elizabeth streb 
ringside company and blondell cummings 
three young italian dance companies will make their american 
debuts they include compagnia efesto paco decina and sosta 
palmizi 
choreographer david gordon will present a new work the 
mysteries and whats so funny featuring music by philip glass 
redden said the visual arts program an apparent source of the 
dispute between menotti and the board will be announced in 
january 
the festival has budgeted a record 800000 for visual arts and 
at menottis direction will be taking risks by trying new forms 
markwardt said 
the exhibits are expected to include large works throughout this 
historic port city and possibly decorating facades of buildings 
the schedule for the jazz and theater offerings will be 
announced later redden said 
