committee agreed that the us applies double standards toward 
saudi arabia 
we do not tolerate cultural differences as an excuse for 
racial violence said schroeder dcolo why do we tolerate it 
for women our young women are being put out there to defend the 
country and are also being told that in off hours they must comply 
with apartheid in that country visavis women 
yard stressed that now opposes iraqs invasion of kuwait but 
says economic sanctions should be given more time to work and that 
a diplomatic solution should be reached through the united nations 
everything president bush is doing leads to war and we are 
opposed to that said yard adding that the military buildup in 
the gulf is designed to protect us oil interests 
now plans to picket the saudi embassy in washington next week 
and will petition the un to condemn the human rights violations 
by the saudi government against women 
