<TEXT>
technicians suspected a problem in the 
manufacture of the hubble space telescopes main mirror but never 
told anyone and the 15 billion instrument was launched with a 
blurred view of the universe investigators said tuesday 
the manufacturer perkinelmer did not assign its best people 
to the telescope construction and there was a surprising lack of 
participation by optical experts with experience in the manufacture 
of large telescopes the investigators final report added 
nasa released the study by a sixmember panel headed by dr lew 
allen director of the space agencys jet propulsion laboratory in 
pasadena calif 
one flaw the panel found echoed a finding of the investigators 
of the 1986 challenger space shuttle accident the hubble report 
said the management structure at perkinelmer raised a strong 
block against communication between people doing handson work 
and higherlevel experts 
in the aftermath of the challenger disaster a lack of 
communication between engineers and upper management was cited as a 
contributing cause 
the telescope launched last april from the space shuttle 
discovery cannot be focused properly because its 
945inchdiameter primary mirror is too flat in the center 
the investigators determined quickly and reiterated in their 
final report that an optical test used in the manufacturing 
process was not set up correctly and thus the surface was 
polished into the wrong shape 
the report said there were clear indications of the problem 
from auxiliary optical tests made at the time but that both 
indicators of error were discounted at the time as being themselves 
flawed 
it said the distortions in the mirror were seen during tests but 
that the manufacturer believed the test was not reliable when in 
fact it was quite accurate enough to detect the gross error and 
indeed did so 
perkinelmer design scientists as well as management for both 
the company and for nasa failed to follow the fabrication process 
with reasonable diligence and were unaware of the flaws the 
report said it did not single out any individuals 
efforts to reach company officials for comment on the report 
were not immediately successful 
the firm which was a leading manufacturer of telescopes used in 
space by the military assigned its most capable optical scientists 
to producing a small demonstration mirror and the design of both 
the hubble mirror and the test apparatus the report said 
but the fabrication of the mirror was the responsibility of the 
optical operations division which operated in a closeddoor 
environment and used neither the optical design scientists or 
available skills outside of the division 
during the testimony it was indicated that some technical 
personnel in the optical operations division were deeply concerned 
at the time that the discrepant optical data might indicate a 
flaw the report said there are no indications that these 
concerns were formally expressed outside this division 
in the grinding of the hubble mirror as in all large telescope 
mirrors a device known as a reflective null corrector is used to 
measure the accuracy of the polishing process the corrector had 
been preserved exactly as it was during the manufacture of the 
mirror and the board found its lens was incorrectly spaced the 
amount of the error would account exactly for the blurred images 
recorded by two cameras on the hubble 
nasa plans to put corrective lenses on the cameras during an 
astronaut visit scheduled for early in 1993 and experts believe 
that will solve the problem even without the corrections the 
hubble has returned some spectacular pictures from space many with 
better resolution than ever seen by groundbased cameras 
</TEXT>
