the fbi cited an exemption under the privacy act in order to 
protect the national defense for not providing lindblom more 
information grossman said 
the lawsuit seeks unedited copies of all material in the file 
destruction of the file an admission that the fbi acted unlawfully 
and monetary damages to be decided by a jury grossman said 
grossman said the material the fbi supplied was so heavily 
edited it was impossible to determine anything about the probe 
except for a newspaper column about lindblom traveling with a south 
korean political dissident 
lindblom said he often travels overseas and his foundation helps 
defend political dissidents on trial in sensitive areas of the 
world but my action is above board 
the foundation is based in suburban niles it has no connection 
with the john d and catherine macarthur foundation although it 
was founded by their son roderick and the two groups support some 
of the same projects lindblom said 
it has made grants totaling 26 million since its founding in 
1976 to other charitable organizations to champion social justice 
lindblom said 
