three years ago jay barbree a space reporter 
who has covered more than 60 manned launches in his 32 years with 
nbc went for a run along the beach near his home in cocoa beach 
fla 
it almost was his last he collapsed and suffered what doctors 
call sudden cardiac death he had no pulse for five minutes 
only quick action by neighbors and paramedics saved him 
frightening but a blessing in disguise had it not happened he 
says odds are that he wouldnt have learned he needed a coronary 
bypass operation a few years later he could have had a definitely 
fatal heart attack 
me dropping dead on the beach is what saved my life thats a 
hell of a thing to say but thats it said barbree who has 
written a justpublished book about his experience the day i 
died 
now 56 barbree the son of a georgia farmer had done his best 
to avoid such an attack 
aware that the men of his family had a history of heart 
problems he had quit smoking 11 years earlier watched his 
cholesterol count avoided highsalt foods and exercised regularly 
all that good stuff 
the scary thing about it is that there was no warning he 
said i was always convinced when i was jogging that if i overdid 
it id have pain in my chest something that said hey jay slow 
down 
but theres a hormone i forget its name that protects you 
against pain and you get whats known as a runners high its 
like a drug you get addicted to it 
in retrospect i was a big idiot down there running like mad 
on the beach it put a bigger demand on my coronary arteries to 
deliver blood to the heart organ than they could sustain 
the arteries were partly blocked by plaque he said he suffered 
the attack a ventricular fibrillation due to their condition 
its like a clogged fuel line he said you can have a 
perfect engine but if it cant get fuel its going to quit 
after a period of recuperation reflection and what is known as 
a petscan an electronic test designed to detect heart disease in 
its earliest stages barbree agreed to coronary bypass surgery 
it was done this month last year he didnt lay about 
afterwards though 
although his work was extremely limited and done at home i 
was back on the air within 30 days said barbree who has covered 
the nations manned space launches since alan shepards first 
suborbital shot in 1961 
now hes back at full power still covering space matters for 
nbc news and the nbc radio network he also occasionally reports 
for some nbcowned stations and the networks affiliates 
coming close to final checkout time tends to make a man think 
differently about things barbree is no exception 
now living in a new home 10 minutes from cape canaveral he 
doesnt jog anymore but i walk briskly now old harry truman 
was right you get out there and walk 
another change before i died i was for capital punishment 
the death penalty now im against it i sort of figure that death 
is gods business now no matter how brutal a crime a man or woman 
commits i simply feel he or she should be locked up forever 
another even though i have a black belt in aikido a 
japanese system of selfdefense i dont think i can hurt 
anybody now but i still have a temper im trying to get under 
control 
and perhaps the most important i really appreciate my family 
my friends people im close to now i just feel closer more 
concerned for them than i ever did before 
 
