late to share the perpetual home repairs aloof neighbors the 
driving everywhere all the time 
pound ridge is a lovely lovely place but it isnt all 
its cracked up to be particularly for a couple that has grown up 
with the excitement of city life said marvin mitzner a partner 
at the new york law firm of davidoff amp malido 
getting out of the city didnt turn out to be what we thought 
it might he said adding that a lot of his friends shared 
similar feelings 
there are no statistics on the number of families abandoning the 
suburbs but the mitzners who have put their home on the market 
are among a group of suburbanites disillusioned by their 
experience 
demographers predicted two decades ago that the baby boomers 
would choose either rural or urban lifestyles this rebellious 
generation sociologists theorized would settle anywhere but in 
the suburbs where they were raised 
the experts were wrong when working couples started families in 
the 1980s many of those who could afford to opted for the suburbs 
as a practical compromise between city and country living 
its a forumula that hasnt worked for everyone 
we were making enough money where we wanted to make an 
investment said deborah hassan who with her husband chose the 
the new york suburb of scarsdale where the median home price is 
535000 within a month after we moved out there our neighbors 
put up a fence it felt so isolated 
before the year was out the hassans and their 3yearold 
daughter were back in manhattan its not easy living in the city 
with a kid said mrs hassan who works part time at american 
express 
but i have this feeling about the city she said theres 
always someone in the park for my daughter to play with 
