<TEXT>
the story of mca inc reads like a hollywood fairy tale about a 
fledgling company that grew from a tiny jazz promoter into a 
conglomerate of movie studios theme parks a bigname record label 
and a publishing house 
the entertainment colossus now represents a chunk of american 
pop culture churning out movie icons ranging from et to 
jaws and making household names out of musicians like guns n 
roses and bobby brown 
but matsushita electric industrial co ltd of japan which 
agreed to purchase mca on monday also bought a company of creative 
visionaries whose screen business has sometimes faltered whose 
movies have been swept up in controversy and whose studios recently 
were ravaged by fire 
mca lived through economic thick and thin to earn a reputation 
as a survivor today mca owns universal studios one of americas 
biggest record labels a publishing house theme parks and big 
piece of los angeles real estate it is known for extremely stable 
management notable in a business famous for capricious and 
unpredictable excecutive changes 
the companys transformation was stagemanaged over a 65year 
history by a chicago eye doctor the late jules stein and lew 
wasserman a onetime movie usher from cleveland wasserman who to 
this day is mcas chairman and president sidney j sheinberg have 
run the company for decades 
over the years universal has produced academy award winners such 
as the sting the deer hunter and out of africa 
but the last temptation of christ stirred up an 
emotioncharged debate inciting religious groups to protest what 
they called its shameful interpretation of biblical history 
more recently the company faced a devastating fire and an 
uncertain market for its feature films 
early this month an arsonist torched the historic universal 
studios backlot gutting sets for dick tracy back to the 
future and an unfinished sylvestor stallone movie 
while universal television has long been a steady moneymaker 
the film division has endured ups and downs its dry spells 
punctuated by periodic blockbusters like et jaws back 
to the future the sting animal house on golden 
pond and twins 
mcas storied history has its roots in the jazz business stein 
a jazz player himself decided musicians needed an agency to strike 
them better deals with hotels ballrooms and speakeasies 
in 1923 he founded the music corporation of america and by the 
1930s mca represented most of the name bands in the swing era 
then stein set his sights on a bigger talent game hollywood 
steins chief aid wasserman proved a dynamo as head of mcas 
hollywood office and soon the agency represented a long list of 
stars including joan crawford errol flynn and alfred hitchcock 
as the major studios shunned television as an upstart 
competitor mca rushed in with its revue productions grinding out 
series like m squad and wagon train when ronald reagans 
film career faded wasserman found him work as host of general 
electric theater 
until 1959 mca was known principally as the octopus because of 
its farreaching influence as a talent agency then the company 
took a giant step buying the venerable faltering universal 
studio 
under wassermans guidance mcauniversal flourished in the 
1970s and 1980s the company became the biggest supplier of 
television entertainment in addition universal studios tours grew 
to a major tourist attraction 
</TEXT>
