<TEXT>
pan american world airways said tuesday it would 
offer cheap winter fares to london in hopes of attracting more 
passengers during the slow winter travel season 
the cashstrapped carrier said passengers who buy tickets by 
dec 7 can get a oneway fare of 149 from new york to london 
based on a roundtrip purchase with fares slightly higher from 
other cities served by pan am 
two of pan ams competitors on the transatlantic flights trans 
world and british airways had no immediate comment on whether they 
intended to slash any fares in response 
airlines usually move quickly to match cheap fares offered by 
rival carriers for fear they could otherwise lose passengers in the 
highly competitive industry 
the pan am fares which are nonrefundable and available on only 
a limited number of seats are good for travel between jan 7 and 
march 21 but the trips must begin by march 14 
the softening of air traffic demand expected during the first 
quarter of 1991 due to weakening economic conditions has prompted 
us to offer winter salfe fares to europe said john bloodworth a 
pan am spokesman we are confident that the fares will stimulate 
traffic during the traditionally slow winter travel period 
pan am is also offering some sale fares to most of its other 33 
destinations in europe 
 
