pepsico inc on tuesday won a court battle to break 
its business relationship with source perrier and take direct 
control of its soft drink operations in france 
the paris commercial court officially recognized that the 
franchise bottling relationship between pepsico and a unit of 
source perrier sa will expire at the end of this year 
the decision clears the way for pepsi cola france sa to take 
direct control of bottling and distributing pepsi brand beverages 
in france at the beginning of next year 
officials at perrier the maker of the wellknown sparking 
mineral water had no immediate comment it was not known whether 
the court ruling would be appealed 
pepsico announced a year ago that it intended to end its 
franchising agreement with perrier stuart haugen managing 
director of pepsi cola france said pepsis market share in france 
had fallen over a decade from 18 percent to 9 percent 
haugen blamed inadequate distribution efforts by perrier 
asserting that pepsi cola clearly wasnt a priority business for 
them he said pepsi cola accounted for only 1 percent to 2 
percent of perriers annual revenue 
perrier said the steady decline in pepsi sales was due to 
insufficient publicity by the us group and its refusal to launch 
diet pepsi a lowcalorie cola on the french market 
perrier said pepsi colas announcement that it intended to break 
off its contract was timed to coincide with a bid by the us 
company to buy perriers softdrink business outright 
perrier sold its softdrink assets to cadburyschweppes plc of 
britain in march 
in may 1989 pepsi colas arch rival cocacola co agreed to 
buy its french bottler from its parent pernodricard sa ending a 
bitter feud between those companies 
