administration chided parker brothers inc tuesday for showing 
insensitivity to modern realities in a game that lists 
supermom and schoolteacher as key careers for girls 
parker brothers is sending the wrong message to young girls 
said sba administrator susan engeleiter even barbie dolls come 
with business suits these days 
careers for girls is a new board game targeted for girls 
ages 812 players select from six careers super mom 
schoolteacher rock star fashion designer college graduate and 
animal doctor 
instructions for the game packaged in a hot pink box include 
show us how you slow dance with your main squeeze describe 
your dream husband tell us the names of your eight children 
and burn all your chocolate chip cooies 
engeleiter said the game shows an insensitivity to modern 
realities in a society where women are making breakthroughs in 
almost every profession im amazed that as we enter the 1990s 
the game doesnt include such careers as business executives 
government leaders astronauts scientists or moms without the 
prefix super 
there are no leadership or policymaking careers on this parker 
brothers game board there are no careers requiring physical daring 
or strength she added noting that women now own 30 percent of 
all businesses in the united states and that the sba projects they 
will own 36 percent by the turn of the century 
company spokesman patricia mcgovern stressed the game is purely 
for entertainment and is certainly not to communicate that only 
certain careers are limited to women the game was designed by a 
woman art was managed by a woman and the product manager was a 
woman she said 
so everyone that was involved with bringing this game to 
market is female said mcgovern were really disappointed to 
hear the objections 
the first to register a complaint with parker brothers about the 
game was washington attorney marna tucker 
i called them up and was infuriated about it said tucker 
i think that right before the holiday season that parker brothers 
is about to step into something very smelly 
tucker said she and a few womens organizations are writing a 
letter demanding that parker brothers either withdraw the game from 
the market or contribute their profits from that to women 
education groups 
they could do a lot of things with the profits that would be 
helpful to women to assist women in breaking down further 
barriers said tucker 
actually careers for girls is an update of a 1957 version 
that listed as professions big business prospecting politics 
going to sea expedition to the moon farming hollywood and 
college mcgovern said the careers were changed in 1971 to include 
ecology space sports teaching and arts career changes were made 
again in 1979 
the game was discontinued in 1984 because it had unfortunately 
lost its mass market appeal said mcgovern we decided to 
reintroduce the game for the 1990s and target it to preteen girls 
because that is a growing niche in the market preteen girls have 
returned to playing board games 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

