<TEXT>
the dollar fell against most major foreign 
currencies tuesday as the british pound boosted by the election of 
john major as the countrys next prime minister dominated the 
foreign exchange markets 
gold prices slipped lower 
the pound surged higher after major chancellor of the exchequer 
the british equivalent of the us treasury was assured of 
becoming the next british prime minster 
major who had the support of outgoing prime minister margaret 
thatcher fell just short of winning election as head of the 
conservative party tuesday but his challengers withdrew from the 
race and conceded defeat to major effectively giving him the prime 
ministers job 
the pound rose to 19775 in new york from 196895 late monday 
in london trading before majors election was assured the pound 
rose to 19750 from 19655 late monday 
foreign exchange traders had hoped major would win because they 
were familiar with his policies and expected little change if he 
succeeded mrs thatcher 
mike faust a currency market annalyst with money market 
services in chicago said sterlings fortune might be shortlived 
he said there was speculation among traders that the british 
government would lower base lending rates to 135 percent from 
their current 14 percent 
currencies are supported by higher interest rates so a drop in 
british rates would make that countrys investments less attractive 
and could send the pound lower 
faust said the dollar fell against other currencies amid the 
belief that the big industrial nations are satisfied with the 
dollars low levels 
in overseas trading the dollar was hurt by a widening of the 
us trade deficit the commerce department said the deficit 
swelled to 2975 billion in the julyseptember quarter up 289 
percent from 2310 billion in the apriljune period 
traders believe the us government will be more inclined to 
keep the dollar lower as a means of narrowing the trade gap a 
lower dollar makes imports into the us more expensive and this 
countrys exports cheaper for overseas buyers 
the dollar fell to 12835 yen in new york from 12905 yen late 
monday in tokyo earlier the dollar rose to 12895 yen from 12795 
yen at mondays close and in london the us currency fell to 
